Event broadcasts at PCSC Stadium
Event broadcasts at PCSC Stadium
Paradise Coast Sports Complex is proud to introduce that selected PCSC Stadium events will now be broadcast
LIVE on the MuscoVision streaming service.
MuscoVision’s system allow for autonomous tracking of on-field action to be followed worldwide by fans of the teams on the field. Available in one-day, three-day, seven-day or 30-day access periods, it is the perfect way to keep up with the action at PCSC Stadium when you can’t be there yourself. Once the action is complete, too, anyone can obtain access to the selected events to enjoy at their leisure!

The Factory – Member Appreciation Day
View this post on Instagram
A post shared by MSM Performance Academy ⚽️ (@msmperformanceacademy)
The Factory Outdoor Gym powered by MSM Performance Academy hosted the first Member Appreciation Day event for all members to enjoy a team work out together. Over 40 members joined the session and continue to show their support and loyalty to the factory.
The Factory and MSM Performance Academy staff and coaches, would like to say thank you to everyone who came out to our Member Appreciation Day! We appreciate your continuous support and loyalty to the Factory. We hope you all enjoyed it, and we hope to see you all again soon! Don’t miss out on the next one!
The next Member Appreciation Day will be on July 26th!
We are hoping to see an even larger turnout of members for a great day of fitness and fun! Join the movement and let’s get better together on July 26th!

2025 FHSAA Lacrosse State Championships
The FHSAA Lacrosse State Championships recently concluded at the esteemed Paradise Coast Sports Complex. The tournament was a showcase of competitive prowess, featuring 16 of Florida’s premier high school lacrosse teams, all vying for the distinct recognition of state champion.
Thousands of spectators joined us for the three-day event, creating a vibrant atmosphere. The competition was intense, but ultimately, only four teams emerged triumphant.
In the boys 2A division, St. Thomas Aquinas High School prevailed over Ponte Vedra High School with a decisive 13-4 victory. This was followed by a thrilling match in the boys 1A division, where The Benjamin School clinched the victory against St. Andrews High School, by a margin of 14-11.
Turning our focus to the girls’ teams, the 2A division featured Plant High School clashing with Lake Mary High School. Plant High School was crowned champions following a 10-7 win. The championship games concluded with a razor-close matchup between American Heritage High School and Lake Highland Prep in the girls’ 1A division, ending 6-5 in favor of Lake Highland Prep.
We extend our sincerest gratitude to FHSAA lacrosse and the assembled teams and spectators for contributing to the success of this event. The Paradise Coast Sports Complex continues to be a venue synonymous with excellence, committed to fostering high-level competition, and honoring athletic achievements. Because ONLY champions play here!

Event Tickets at PCSC
Event Tickets at PCSC
Tickets for events at the Paradise Coast Sports Complex
There are numerous types of events held at the Paradise Coast Sports Complex.  Some are put on the PCSC and it’s partners/sponsors and some are put on by private entities that rent out the facility.  You should be aware of the type of event that you are coming to when visiting the complex.
Most community events, although not all of them, put on by PCSC and it’s partners/sponsors, like holiday festivals and the like, are free to attend (Fall Fest, Snow Fest, Eggstravaganza, etc.).  Although, please keep in mind, there may be areas of the park or parts of the event or even private vendor areas that have charges to them.
PLEASE NOTE:
Other events, like concerts, sports tournaments, club tournaments and semi-pro sporting events rent the facilities from PCSC and may charge fees for entry into those events.  Those are not controlled by PCSC or our staff and quite often will have a separate website to purchase tickets in advance.
When we know of events that have other websites to purchase tickets in advance, we will put a link to those websites further below on this page.  Thank you.
